President Trump held a press conference in the Rose Garden where he discussed a range of topics, including his relationship with Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, tax reform, healthcare, and his response to the hurricane aftermath in Puerto Rico. He also addressed questions about the Iran deal, the Russia investigation, and the controversy surrounding NFL players kneeling during the national anthem. Trump expressed his support for an economic development bill and discussed his upcoming trips to Asia. He also commented on the recent clashes between Kurdish and Iraqi forces in northern Iraq.